# s&box visual content

When authoring landscapes, buildings, furniture, creatures, trees, or props:

1. Follow the `sbox-asset-authoring` skill (kit / mesh / place / look router).
2. Use `tools/sbox-asset-harness/` catalogs — do not invent `.vmdl` / `.vmat` paths.
3. Reuse the active game’s `MeshPrimitives` / scenery helpers; otherwise copy from `tools/sbox-asset-harness/portable/SceneKit/`.
4. Center-pivoted primitives must be lifted so the bottom sits on the ground; coplanar faces get ~±1 unit nudge — no large floating Z bands.
5. Update catalog JSON in the same change. Run `powershell -File tools/sbox-asset-harness/scripts/validate_catalog.ps1` when catalogs change (or the `.py` script if Python exists).
